"```sql\nSELECT r.year, r.name, res.points\nFROM drivers d\nJOIN results res ON d.driverId = res.driverId\nJOIN races r ON res.raceId = r.raceId\nWHERE d.forename = 'Lewis' AND d.surname = 'Hamilton'\nORDER BY r.year, r.date\nLIMIT 1;\n```\n\nThis SQL query retrieves the year, race name, and points recorded for Lewis Hamilton's first race. It joins the `drivers`, `results`, and `races` tables to find the relevant information, ordering by year and date to ensure the first race is selected."